              "note": "$v(2) = 6.10$ m s$^{-1}$ $(6.09520\\ldots)$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$6.10$ m s$^{-1}$",
          "solution": "$$v(2) = 10e^{-0.4}\\sin 2 = 6.09520 \\approx 6.10 \\text{ m s}^{-1}.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(10*exp(Rational(-2,5))*sin(2) - 6.10) < 0.0051"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Find the maximum velocity of the particle.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "maximise with the GDC (or solve $v'(t) = 0$, i.e. $\\tan t = 5$, giving $t = 1.37$)"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$v_{max} = 7.45$ m s$^{-1}$ $(7.45060\\ldots)$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$7.45$ m s$^{-1}$",
          "solution": "$v'(t) = 10e^{-0.2t}(\\cos t - 0.2\\sin t) = 0$ gives $\\tan t = 5$, so $t = \\arctan 5 = 1.37340$ and$$v_{max} = 7.45060 \\approx 7.45 \\text{ m s}^{-1}.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(atan(5) - 1.37) < 0.0051",
