          "marks": 3,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "distance $= \\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi} |v(t)|\\,dt$, and $v \\ge 0$ on the interval"
            },
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "evaluate the integral with the GDC"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "distance $= 14.7$ m $(14.7451\\ldots)$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$14.7$ m",
          "solution": "$\\sin t \\ge 0$ on $[0, \\pi]$, so $v \\ge 0$ and$$\\text{distance} = \\int_0^{\\pi} 10e^{-0.2t}\\sin t\\,dt = 14.7451 \\approx 14.7 \\text{ m}.$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(integrate(10*exp(-t/5)*sin(t), (t, 0, pi)) - 14.7) < 0.051000000000000004"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "A particle moves in a straight line. Its velocity in m s$^{-1}$ at time $t$ seconds is $v(t) = 10e^{-0.2t}\\sin t$ for $0 \\le t \\le \\pi$."
